## Security in Midtrans
---

##### *Security is our top priority in Midtrans. We monitor the internal and external factors to ensure the security of your payment is going to Midtrans.*
------------------

### Midtrans Security

1. **PCI DSS**<br>
	PCI-DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard) is a certificate or license issued by the PCI Security Standards Council to maintain security activities transactions processed through Midtrans payment systems. Midtrans have implemented security standards set by the PCI Standard Council on the network and payment systems so we can minimize any security risk that could interfere with the process of the transactions that occur on our system.

	Midtrans been audited by the auditor PCI-certified and certified for [PCI Service Provider Level 1](http://www.visa.com/splisting/searchGrsp.do?companyNameCriteria=midtrans). This is the most stringent level of certification available in the payments industry.

2. **ISO 27001**<br>
	ISO27001 (or commonly known as ISO / IEC 27001) is a certificate or license issued by the Internal Standards Organization (ISO), which regulates security management information system. We have implemented the ISO27001 standard set by the system and our network to maintain the security of any information we have.

3. **AES 256**<br>
	AES (Advanced Encryption Standard) is an encryption standard that was issued by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST), which is generally used to maintain the confidentiality of the data. We use as standard AES-256 encryption for all data transactions into and out of our system.

4. **Fraud Detection System**<br>
	Midtrans analyze in detail each transaction processed, which is then processed and managed using machine learning. After these two steps, Midtrans can analyze the behavior patterns of the location pay, limited hours, and a specific email.

	Source: [https://midtrans.com/security](https://midtrans.com/security)

